{"cursor":"10999","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"In media industry jargon, \"'development hell'\" (or \"'development limbo'\") is a\nperiod during which a film or other project is trapped in development. A film,\ntelevision program, screenplay, computer program, concept, or idea\nstranded in development hell takes an especially long time to start production,\nor never does.\n\nThe film industry buys rights to many popular novels, video games, and comics,\nbut it may take years for such properties to be successfully brought to the\ncinema, and often with considerable changes to the plot, characters, and general\ntone.\n","linknr":198,"url":"Development_hell","recorded":1362477581,"links":17,"instances":["fiction","film","series","musical","filmmaking","2009_film","2003_film","film","video_game"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Film production","Vaporware"],"headings":["Overview","Related concepts","Examples","See also","References"],"image":["//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["development","film"],["turnaround","filmmaking"],["akira","film#live_action_film"],["akira","film#live_action_film"],["hulk","2003_film"],["independence_day","film#sequels"],["jurassic_park","franchise#jurassic_park_iv"],["les_misérables","2012_film_"],["les_misérables","2012_film"],["les_misérables","musical"],["the_postman","film"],["sadness","video_game"],["soul","series"],["reboot","fiction"],["watchmen","2009_film"],["turnaround","filmmaking"]],"members":["reboot","the_postman","akira","soul","les_misérables","jurassic_park","turnaround","watchmen","independence_day","hulk","development","sadness"],"related":["Media_industry","Jargon","Development_(film)","Film","Television_program","Screenplay","Computer_program","Film_production","Film_rights","Screenwriter","Film_producer","Film_st